snippet: Two senior members of an ultranationalist party were charged by the authorities on Friday for their involvement in violent clashes this week in Kiev.
abstract: Ukrainian authorities charge Igor Shvayka and Yuriy Syrotyuk, senior members of far-right anti-Russian party Svoboda, for alleged involvement in violent protest near Parliament in Kiev that left three police officers dead.
lead_paragraph: Two senior members of an ultranationalist party were charged by the authorities on Friday for their involvement in violent clashes this week in Kiev.

headline.main: Ukraine: Two Ultranationalists Are Charged Over Clashes in Kiev
